..TEXT:
|segno~: From the Latin ^signum~, |segno~ means the
"ensign" of the Roman Empire, its banner.  Cf. ^Par.~ VI, 32.
|laude~ = ^lodi.~  The term is used here to mean those souls who
declare God's grace and glory by their very actions.  See ^Inf.~
II, 103 (where this is said of Beatrice) and the note.
