..TEXT:
|non pot$e suo valor~... |eccesso~: This should
not be understood as derogating from God's power (as if He could
not do this or that), but rather as being to His greater glory,
since His worth necessarily exceeds all created things (even
though these are created by Him), as does His wisdom (|verbo~).
"Cf. XIII, 52-78.  God's ideal conception is infinite, while the
created universe is finite" (Gr).  |verbo~: Cf. ^Par.~ XVIII, 1.
