|Lume non @e~: "There is no light," i.e., no light
for the human intellect.  |dal sereno~... |mai~: From the
eternally serene light of God.  |anzi @e ten@ebra~... |veleno~:
Without grace (God's light), all that we take to be light is
darkness, either the shadow or the poison of the flesh, either
ignorance or vice.
