|e tutti suoi voleri~... |sermoni~: |Voleri~
looks to the will of the inner man and |atti~ to his outward
deeds, the key phrase being |quanto ragione umana vede~, which
clearly implies that our human view and understanding of the case
may indeed be a limited one.  |in vita o in sermoni~: Cf. Luc.
24:19: "vir propheta potens in opere et sermone" ("a prophet,
mighty in work and word").
