..TEXT:
|Praga~: Prague, on the Moldau (now Vltava), the
capital of Bohemia.  The allusion is to the invasion of the
dominions of Wenceslaus II, king of Bohemia, in 1304 by his
brother-in-law, Albert I (Wenceslaus having married, as his first
wife, Albert's sister).  Albert was jealous of the growing power
of Bohemia and wanted to force Wenceslaus to renounce the claim
of his son Wenceslaus to the throne of Hungary in favor of
Charles Robert, eldest son of Charles Martel.  (See Map 1, facing
p. 162.)
