..TEXT:
|quei che guarda l'isola del foco~: Frederick II,
king of the volcanic island of Sicily.  Cf. ^Purg.~ VII, 119;
^Conv.~ IV, vi, 20; ^De vulg. eloqu.~ I, xii, 5.  After warring
for some years with Charles II of Naples, he made peace with him
and married one of his daughters.  Upon the death of Emperor
Henry VII, he abandoned the Ghibelline cause.
