..TEXT:
|e a dare~... |loco~: "To indicate at the same
time his insignificance and his wickedness, his many misdeeds
shall be recorded in shorthand" (Gr).  The anaphora shifts now to
tercets beginning with ^e.~  Thus it is first ^l~, then ^v~
(interchangeable with ^u~), then ^e.~  The term ^lue~ is thus
spelled out, which as a noun (^la lue~) means "pestilence."  For
a similar device, see ^Purg.~ XII, 25-63 and the note to
^Purg.~ XII, 61-63.
