..TEXT:
|O beata Ungheria~... |malmenare~: The throne
of Hungary, which belonged to Charles Martel (^Par.~ VIII,
64-66), was usurped by Andrew III.  |e beata Navarra~...
|fascia~: "Navarre would be happy if she could protect herself
with the mountain chains that enfold her -- that is, if she could
make the Pyrenees a bulwark against France, which is destined to
annex her on the death of her queen, Joanna, married to Philip
the Fair" (Gr).
